  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nAs a Validator switching to teku, I want to be able to have a low-friction process for migrating. The scariest step of the migration (for me at least), is the one about importing slashing protection data from another client. I would like t be able to read the documentation, and to feel like this is something easy to do, and that many people have passed this way before.\r\n\r\nCurrently, the documentation indicates to run the command:\r\n```\r\nteku slashing-protection import --data-path=/home/me/me_node --from=/home/slash/slashing-interchange-format.json\r\n```\r\nIt further describes:\r\n\r\n- `--data-path` specifies the location of the Teku `data` directory.`\r\n\r\nIt is not clear what this means.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2212651/133792589-0ef8be57-e6b3-43d7-a7e1-53bcd6f9822e.png)\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nFor it to be unambiguous as to what command to run.",
